listData.name: Retail Term Deposit
listData.description: Term Deposit. Enjoy guaranteed returns with ME's Term Deposit. There's no set-up fees and no account-keeping fees.

features.additionalInfo: Deposits are protected by the Australian Government's Financial Claims Scheme, up to $250,000 per person per authorised deposit taking institution.
ATM REFUNDS. Use any ATM, anywhere in Australia, and we'll refund your ATM fees usually within 5 minutes.
KEEP YOUR CASH. Banking with zero monthly account-keeping fees. You earned it, you spend it.

NO MINIMUM DEPOSIT.
It's your money; we won't tell you what to do with it. Say yes to convenience, no to obligations.

constraints.additionalInfo: Rates are for deposits between $5,000 and $2,000,000. For rates for amounts above $2,000,0000, contact ME on 13 15 63.

eligibility.additionalValue: An Australian citizen, permanent resident or Australian resident for tax purposes

eligibility.additionalInfo: The account should be used in personal capacity or for personal use. It must not be opened or used for business or trustee perposes

detailData.name: Retail Term Deposit
detailData.description: Term Deposit. Enjoy guaranteed returns with ME's Term Deposit. There's no set-up fees and no account-keeping fees.

listData.name: Flexible Home Loan with Member Package
listData.description: All the features of a ME Flexible Home Loan with added Member Package benefits like lower variable rates and reduced fees.

features.additionalInfo:
If have a variable loan you can make as many extra payments as you want, with no penalty whatsoever.
If you're on a fixed rate loan, you can make up to $30,000 in extra payments during the fixed rate period; going above that amount will attract a penalty fee. (Of course, once the loan reverts to a variable rate, there's no extra payment limit.)
Member Package. For just $395 per year, add a Member Package to your Flexible Home Loan and receive lower variable and fixed interest rates, no valuation fee, no top up fee.
Internet banking and mobile app
Free redraws on variable home loans if you're ahead on payments (minimum $500).
Offset account. Let your savings reduce your interest with a 100% offset account.
Pay interest-only. You can pay just the interest for up to 5 years on a home you'll live in, and request up to an additional 5 years if it's an investment property.
Fixed loan prepayments. Pay up to $30k into the fixed portion of your home loan during the fixed rate period, without incurring a prepayment fee.
Repayment holiday. Apply to take a break from repayments when the unexpected happens, if you're ahead on your repayments.
Rate lock. You can add a rate lock option to your fixed home loan application for $500 which lets you hedge against rates rising before the settlement date.

eligibility.additionalInfo: Home loan applications are subject to the Bank's normal credit approval.

eligibility.additionalValue: A citizen or permanent resident of Australia or a citizen of New Zealand that is permanently residing in Australia and employed (where applicable) in Australia.

fees.name: Member package fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable if you choose to purchase a Member Package, at settlement, and on each anniversary.

fees.name: Valuation fee
fees.additionalInfo: If a valuation is needed, this fee is charged per property and covers some of our cost.

fees.name: Valuation fee
fees.additionalInfo: If a valuation is needed, this fee is charged per property and covers some of our cost.

fees.name: Agent fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable at or before settlement if our external solicitors are required to instruct an agent to conduct settlement (e.g. if in a rural area)

fees.name: Settlement fee
fees.additionalInfo: This fee (currently $250) covers some of the costs associated with establishing and settling your home loan. This fee is payable at settlement.

fees.name: Government fees and charges
fees.additionalInfo: Government fees and charges. Differ by state.

fees.name: Rate lock fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable if you elect to lock in a fixed interest rate.

fees.name: Lenders Mortgage Insurance (LMI)
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when the loan amount is greater than 80% of the property's value.

fees.name: Top up fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when you top-up your home loan.

fees.name: Security substitution fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable if we approve a request to substitute the security property for another property.

fees.name: Bank cheque fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable if we provide you with a bank cheque, repurchase a bank cheque or replace a bank cheque.

fees.name: Telegraphic transfer fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when you request us to make a payment for you via Telegraphic Transfer.

fees.name: Production of title fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable to produce the title to the security property.

fees.name: Arrears fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable on the fifth day after: a loan facility has missed a scheduled payment and fallen into arrears, and/or; each month (or every four weeks if your payment frequency is weekly or fortnightly) that the loan remains in arrears.

fees.name: Security discharge preparation fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable on discharge of a mortgage. Charged per property.

fees.name: Prepayment fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable if we incur a loss due to the early termination of a fixed interest rate period.

fees.name: Search fees
fees.additionalInfo: It may be necessary to conduct title or instrument searches or property enquiries. If so, you must pay us at or before settlement the actual cost incurred for such searches or enquiries.

fees.name: Consent to a dealing fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when we consent to a dealing with a property.

fees.name: Subdivision approval valuation fee
fees.additionalInfo: Subdivision approval valuation fee.  Cost varies.

listData.name: Flexible Home Loan
listData.description: Offset accounts, early repayments and free redraw, the Flexible Home Loan gives you plenty of options to tinker with.

features.additionalInfo: Internet banking and mobile app
Free redraws on variable home loans if you're ahead on payments (minimum $500).
Offset account. Let your savings reduce your interest with a 100% offset account.
Pay interest-only. You can pay just the interest for up to 5 years on a home you'll live in, and request up to an additional 5 years if it's an investment property.
Repayment holiday. Apply to take a break from repayments when the unexpected happens, if you're ahead on your repayments.
Rate lock. You can add a rate lock option to your fixed home loan application for $500 which lets you hedge against rates rising before the settlement date.
Fix or split. There is no fee to fix or split your loan.

To receive $2K cashback offer, apply from 8 September 2023 and settle within 120 days of the loan application date.  Switch your existing home loan from another lender. Take out a home loan with a minimum size of $400k and maximum LVR of 80%.

To receive $3K cashback offer, apply from 8 September 2023 and settle within 120 days of the loan application date.  Switch your existing home loan from another lender. Take out a home loan with a minimum size of $700k and maximum LVR of 80%.

eligibility.additionalInfo: Home loan applications are subject to the Bank's normal credit approval.

listData.name: Basic Home Loan
listData.description: ME's Basic Home Loan: One low variable rate, no application fee and zero monthly account-keeping fees.

features.additionalInfo: Pay weekly, fortnightly or monthly.
Pay interest-only. You can pay just the interest for up to 5 years on a home you'll live in, and request up to an additional 5 years if it's an investment property.

To receive $2K cashback offer, apply from 8 September 2023 and settle within 120 days of the loan application date.  Switch your existing home loan from another lender. Take out a home loan with a minimum size of $400k and maximum LVR of 80%.

To receive $3K cashback offer, apply from 8 September 2023 and settle within 120 days of the loan application date.  Switch your existing home loan from another lender. Take out a home loan with a minimum size of $700k and maximum LVR of 80%.

If you have a variable loan you can make as many extra payments as you want, with no penalty whatsoever.
If you're on a fixed rate loan, you can make up to $30,000 in extra payments during the fixed rate period; going above that amount will attract a penalty fee. (Of course, once the loan reverts to a variable rate, there's no extra payment limit.)

listData.name: Everyday Transaction Account
listData.description: ME's Everyday Transaction Account gives you everything you need for day-to-day banking, all for a monthly account-keeping fee of $0 (thats zero, zip, nada). And your choice of 5 card colours.

features.additionalInfo: Can be used anywhere EFTPOS is accepted.
SAVE MORE. Open an Online Savings Account with your Everyday Transaction Account and you could earn a bank-load of bonus interest.
Put a temporary stop on your card whenever you need to - instantly in the app and internet banking.
Internet banking and mobile app
Deposits are protected by the Australian Government's Financial Claims Scheme, up to $250,000 per person per authorised deposit taking institution.
When you use your Pink Buck card, ME will donate 1 cent for every transaction to the National Breast Cancer Foundation.
Receive fast payments, 24/7, from a number of financial institutions.  Sending payments via the New Payment Platform is not currently available.
Apple Pay allows you to use your compatible iPhone and Apple Watch to pay securely in shops, and also iPad and Mac within apps and on the web using Safari, instead of your physical card.
By adding your card to the Google Pay app, you can make purchases in store and online using your compatible Android device.
By adding your card to Fitbit Pay via the Fitbit app, you can make purchases in store using your compatible device.
By adding your card to Garmin Pay via the Garmin app, you can make purchases in store using your compatible device.
By adding your card to the Samsung Pay app, you can make purchases in store and online using your compatible device.
Use your mobile number or email address to receive PayID payments  no more remembering BSB and account numbers.  Sending payments to a PayID is not currently available.
